&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Bertram Capital, a Foster City, CA-based private equity investment firm, is seeking a highly organized and detail-oriented Coordinator to provide day-to-day operational and administrative support to its OCM team. The ideal candidate is dependable, proactive, and skilled at managing competing priorities in a fast-paced, collaborative environment. The Coordinator will serve as the operational backbone of the OCM team, maintaining the Salesforce.com database, coordinating scheduling and travel, processing expenses, and producing routine reports. Approximately 75% of the Coordinator’s time will be dedicated to administrative and operational support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate all travel arrangements for the OCM team, including flights, hotels, and ground transportation, ensuring smooth and timely logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate day-to-day calendars and scheduling for the OCM team, proactively resolving conflicts and prioritizing meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, process, and submit expense reports on behalf of the OCM team, ensuring accuracy and adherence to company policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the end-to-end non-disclosure agreement (NDA) process on behalf of the OCM team
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for LexCheck, the firm’s AI-powered NDA review solution, coordinating submissions and managing the review workflow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate communication and negotiation of NDA terms between the firm’s OCM and counterparty investment bankers and attorneys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate, track, and ensure that agreed NDA terms are accurately communicated, implemented, and monitored on an ongoing basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Compliance to coordinate all requests for destruction of confidential materials in accordance with NDA obligations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the Salesforce.com database on an ongoing basis, ensuring records are complete, accurate, and current across all OCM activities
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the refinement of Salesforce.com data entry and reporting workflows, and assist in tracking deal pipeline activity as opportunities progress through the OCM process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and organize recurring reports and activity summaries within Salesforce.com to help the OCM team track outreach progress and deal pipeline status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all information entered in Salesforce.com is kept current and accurately reflects the firm’s OCM activities and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and distribute a defined set of OCM reports on a weekly, monthly, and quarterly basis to keep the team informed of activity levels, pipeline status, and outreach progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
